{
  "texts": [
    "This is similar to weak adversarial networks, but instead formulated using the strong form.",
    "AnsatzAnother prominent topic is the question of which ansatz to choose.",
    "The type of ansatz is, for example, determined by different NN architectures (see [261] for a comparison) or combinations with classical ansatz formulations.",
    "Instead of using FC-NNs, some authors [182,226] employ CNNs to exploit the spatial structure of the data.",
    "Irregular geometries can be handled by embedding the structure in a rectangular domain using binary encodings [262] or signed distance functions [86,263]."
  ]
}